      <div class="col-sm-7">
        <h2></h2>
        
            <div class="gen-group">
              
                <div class="gen-group__logo"><img src="https://d1o1wdbk5ytaqh.cloudfront.net/media/Screen_Shot_2015-09-23_at_11.26.59.png" /></div>
              
              <div class="gen-group__content">
                <p class="subheading">Site managed by</p>
                <h2>Penpont Farm Solar</h2>
              </div>
            </div>
        
        <div class="gen-content">
          <p>Penpont Farm Solar gives the Hawkey Family a diversified income to support bird, flora and fauna wildlife on the farm, owned by the family for the last three generations. </p>
<p>The Hawkey Family first bought the farm in 1915. The farm business has grown and diversified over the last 100 years. Brothers Shaun and Oliver Hawkey, now run two businesses on the family farm - Oliver runs the 550 acre working farm with 100kW solar, while Shaun runs The Olde House, a self-catering farmstay holiday business with <a href="http://piclo.uk/p/the-olde-house-solar/PjEUm">The Olde House Solar</a> installed to help power the business. </p>
<p>Taking a green approach, Penpont Farm is part of Natural England’s Higher Level Stewardship. This scheme affects many of the farm’s activities; hedges are trimmed at certain times of the year to allow for nesting birds, some fields aren’t ploughed to leave wild habitats, woodlands are planted, and a selection of fields are flooded to extend bird sanctuary habitat. </p>
<p>Revenue generated by export electricity from the 100kW solar installation goes back into the farm - so far this income has paid for maintenance, new machinery and financed a new workshop.</p>
          <p class="read-more"><a href="#" class="button">Read More</a></p>
        </div>
        

